♪

02:16.484 --> 02:18.399
- Hey.

02:24.274 --> 02:25.667
[tearing fabric]

02:35.285 --> 02:37.157
♪ There's no--

02:37.200 --> 02:40.116
[metal music]

02:40.160 --> 02:44.207
♪ Open your eyes to the source
of the universe ♪

02:44.251 --> 02:45.600
- You know we couldn't
have been more

02:45.643 --> 02:47.428
than 15 minutes behind him.

02:47.471 --> 02:49.517
I mean, they left
all their shit, bro.

02:49.560 --> 02:51.475
They must've just left.

02:51.519 --> 02:53.738
And that contraband.
Ooh.

02:53.782 --> 02:56.001
I bet you there's more
where that came from.

02:56.045 --> 02:58.178
No.
No.

02:58.221 --> 02:59.831
That's a high-traffic area.

02:59.875 --> 03:03.008
We need to get back there.
Yeah.

03:03.052 --> 03:07.012
- The Founding Fathers of
course were committed pagans.

03:07.056 --> 03:10.059
That is why D.C. is built
on a pentagram,

03:10.102 --> 03:14.019
one point each for the four
traditional can of jars.=:

03:14.063 --> 03:18.241
stomach, intestines,
lungs, liver.

03:18.285 --> 03:20.591
But what did
they forget about?

03:20.635 --> 03:23.507
The fifth point.
The brain.

03:23.551 --> 03:26.467
[acoustic guitar strumming]

03:26.510 --> 03:28.860
[radio chatter]

03:28.904 --> 03:31.646
- The average size is smaller
than a grain of rice.

03:37.869 --> 03:39.262
It's a lot of paperwork.

03:39.306 --> 03:41.221
- Just take it easy
on the people.

03:41.264 --> 03:42.831
- All right, Papa.

03:42.874 --> 03:44.789
Just like you take it easy
on me, right?

03:44.833 --> 03:46.748
- [laughs]

03:48.750 --> 03:51.013
These dishes in here aren't
gonna wash themselves.

03:52.841 --> 03:54.146
- [sighs]

03:54.190 --> 03:55.539
- Just a reminder,
San Bonifacio schools

03:55.583 --> 03:57.062
will be cancelled Friday,

03:57.106 --> 03:58.847
and the annual class breakfast
at the fire station

03:58.890 --> 04:01.676
will be rebranded
as breakfast or dinner.

04:01.719 --> 04:03.721
The high tomorrow is 107,

04:03.765 --> 04:05.767
so don't look into that
noonday sun,

04:05.810 --> 04:07.812
or you will go blind.
It's just common sense.

04:07.856 --> 04:10.511
In other news, following up
on our breaking story,

04:10.554 --> 04:12.034
police have declared
a full curfew

04:12.077 --> 04:14.515
as they search for suspected
bomber, Floyd Ferness.

04:14.558 --> 04:18.083
[funky music]

04:18.127 --> 04:22.479
♪ Oh, yeah

04:22.523 --> 04:25.482
- ♪ They say
that into each life ♪

04:25.526 --> 04:27.745
♪ Some rain must fall

04:27.789 --> 04:30.095
♪ And that tears
is only rain ♪

04:30.139 --> 04:32.707
♪ To make love bloom

04:32.750 --> 04:36.754
♪ But I've been crying days

04:36.798 --> 04:40.105
♪ And all I've got
to show for it ♪

04:40.149 --> 04:42.412
♪ Is a slow-paced love

04:42.456 --> 04:46.938
♪ Tears can't help me find

04:46.982 --> 04:49.289
♪ Answers to the problems you
left behind ♪

04:49.332 --> 04:51.552
♪ Ooh,
honey ♪

04:51.595 --> 04:54.250
♪ Tears can't help me hide

04:54.294 --> 04:56.165
♪ Tears can't help me hide

04:56.208 --> 04:58.428
♪ This emptiness
that I feel inside ♪

04:58.472 --> 05:01.257
♪ Ooh

05:01.301 --> 05:04.347
[vultures cawing]

05:06.741 --> 05:09.091
- Mr. Mayor.
Cherry Vista is cordoned off.

05:09.134 --> 05:11.615
We got a dragnet down
in Packingtown.

05:11.659 --> 05:13.095
And, uh,

05:13.138 --> 05:15.750
you know, Ferness playing
hide-and-seek for the last 48.

05:15.793 --> 05:17.621
- So arrest
his cop-killing ass.

05:17.665 --> 05:19.754
I've been asking
for this manhunt all week.

05:19.797 --> 05:21.364
- Well, we didn't have
a suspect.

05:21.408 --> 05:23.366
- Eve, this is a campaign here.

05:23.410 --> 05:27.022
How can I be tough on crime if
you don't catch the criminals?

05:27.065 --> 05:29.067
The people want spectacle.

05:29.111 --> 05:31.461
Choppers with the spotlights.

05:31.505 --> 05:33.463
Where are my choppers, Eve?

05:33.507 --> 05:34.899
- Tony,
let's not do this again.

05:34.943 --> 05:36.510
- Do what?

05:36.553 --> 05:39.034
Remind you that your job is
to make me fucking look good?

05:40.252 --> 05:43.995
Eve, you ever see Ferness
on the open field?

05:44.039 --> 05:46.955
Damn, that boy could juke
like nobody's business.

05:46.998 --> 05:48.957
Calves like
fucking border houses.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.438
- We'll get him, Tony.
He's one man.

05:51.481 --> 05:53.396
- One man with an all-county
rushing record.

05:53.440 --> 05:57.052
One man you put on the force.
- After you insisted on it.

05:57.095 --> 05:59.837
- He's supposed to be a role
model, not a goddamn maniac.

06:02.884 --> 06:07.149
Eve, I've got a fundraiser
to go to this afternoon.

06:07.192 --> 06:09.499
Now, I would like to spend it

06:09.543 --> 06:12.372
drinking 12-year-old scotch

06:12.415 --> 06:15.157
and raking in
100-year-old money.

06:15.200 --> 06:18.508
Now, do you think you can
collar Ferness?

06:18.552 --> 06:22.904
Or do I have to get up on a car

06:22.947 --> 06:25.820
with a bullhorn
and remind people

06:25.863 --> 06:30.128
what real fucking leadership
looks like?!

06:30.172 --> 06:32.435
[splat]
The fuck?

06:32.479 --> 06:33.741
[vulture caws]

06:33.784 --> 06:36.047
Ugh!

06:36.091 --> 06:37.875
- Gene, there you are.

06:37.919 --> 06:39.268
Uh, Tony,

06:39.311 --> 06:41.313
this is Captain Gene Colder,
homicide.

06:41.357 --> 06:42.793
He's heading up things
on the ground.

06:42.837 --> 06:44.447
- This is more like it.

06:44.491 --> 06:46.449
Nice to meet you, young man.
Beer?

06:46.493 --> 06:47.972
- Sticking to unleaded.

06:48.016 --> 06:50.192
- Mr. Mayor,
take our word for it.

06:50.235 --> 06:53.717
It's a show of quiet strength
if you leave things to us.

06:53.761 --> 06:57.547
- I like loud strength, Eve.
Loud!

06:58.505 --> 06:59.680
What do you think, Captain?

07:03.423 --> 07:04.554
- We got this.

07:04.598 --> 07:06.948
- See, that's what
I like to hear, Eve.

07:06.991 --> 07:08.471
Decisiveness.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.952
Power.
Balls.

07:10.995 --> 07:12.780
Speaking of which...

07:14.956 --> 07:16.218
Oh, shit.

07:18.829 --> 07:19.874
- [sighs]

07:22.224 --> 07:24.922
[exciting music]

07:24.966 --> 07:26.794
- I'm Ginger Galanti,
coming to you live

07:26.837 --> 07:28.970
from the San Bonifacio
police headquarters

07:29.013 --> 07:31.668
where Chief Eve Raytek
is set to address the media.

07:31.712 --> 07:33.322
Let's go to her now.

07:33.365 --> 07:34.976
- After this week's
double car bombing

07:35.019 --> 07:37.587
which cost my department
two of its finest,

07:37.631 --> 07:41.461
we are declaring a manhunt
for Floyd Ferness.

07:41.504 --> 07:43.245
He's a former officer
with a grudge,

07:43.288 --> 07:45.987
and he is--forgive my French--
a dangerous son of a gun.

07:46.030 --> 07:47.118
- [clears throat]

07:47.162 --> 07:49.294
You've must've met
Floyd Ferness.

07:49.338 --> 07:51.166
- Had drinks with him
and Felicity once or twice.

07:51.209 --> 07:54.648
He's--intense guy.

07:55.344 --> 07:57.302
- I met him yesterday.

07:57.346 --> 07:58.652
- What?

07:58.695 --> 08:00.305
- I chased him through
a zoo parking lot.

08:00.349 --> 08:03.047
He got away.
- He got--

08:03.091 --> 08:04.135
Jesus Christ.

08:05.572 --> 08:07.095
- Okay.
Be cool, you're my lawyer.

08:09.010 --> 08:10.664
- And as your lawyer
I'd advise you

08:10.707 --> 08:13.057
to stop consorting
with murder suspects.

08:13.101 --> 08:16.147
- I'm not that sure
that he's guilty.

08:16.191 --> 08:19.150
Freddie Laffter said those
bombs were out-of-town talent.

08:19.194 --> 08:22.589
Floyd's not an out-of-town guy.
Or that talented.

08:22.632 --> 08:24.242
What'd you bring me?

08:24.286 --> 08:26.157
- I've been closing out
Felicity's accounts.

08:26.201 --> 08:29.117
Thankfully,
she kept things simple.

08:29.160 --> 08:32.555
Automated payments.
Not much credit card debt.

08:32.599 --> 08:33.991
What are you looking for?

08:34.035 --> 08:36.298
- Going through people's lives
is my business.

08:36.341 --> 08:38.169
I start by asking myself,

08:38.213 --> 08:40.432
what is this person
showing the world

08:40.476 --> 08:42.652
and what are they hiding?

08:42.696 --> 08:44.480
I need to know what Felicity
was hiding.

08:44.524 --> 08:46.003
- A second apartment.

08:46.047 --> 08:47.527
- She didn't live
in that complex.

08:47.570 --> 08:48.615
Strucker confirmed it.

08:48.658 --> 08:50.660
What's, uh--
what's this?

08:50.704 --> 08:52.444
- Autopay.
What's Culpa-conn?

08:52.488 --> 08:53.837
- Oh,
it's a local cell provider.

08:53.881 --> 08:55.926
Their service is trash,
but they cheap.

08:55.970 --> 08:57.667
- So where's her burner phone?

08:57.711 --> 09:01.236
- Let's call Culpa-conn
and see.

09:03.673 --> 09:06.589
- [sighs]

09:06.633 --> 09:09.505
[mysterious music]

09:09.549 --> 09:16.251
♪

09:23.388 --> 09:24.999
- No dice.

09:25.042 --> 09:27.915
I need a notarized request
to access the account.

09:32.615 --> 09:34.965
Did you order that?

09:35.009 --> 09:36.967
- A Greek.

09:38.752 --> 09:41.276
He would always put one piece
of fresh fruit

09:41.319 --> 09:43.147
on the top of the dumpster.

09:43.191 --> 09:45.802
For me.

09:45.846 --> 09:47.108
- Felicity never told me that--

09:47.151 --> 09:49.719
- That's because
she didn't know.

09:51.112 --> 09:52.940
I did it so
she wouldn't have to.

09:55.507 --> 09:57.205
So the phone's a dead end?

09:57.248 --> 09:59.337
- Well, there's always ways.
I mean, we'd be better off

09:59.381 --> 10:01.209
finding somebody with influence
to grease the wheels.

10:01.252 --> 10:04.299
- Jake Spivey invited me
to a party today.

10:04.342 --> 10:07.737
Seems to be running
with a powerful crowd.

10:07.781 --> 10:10.566
- You know Spivey?
- I know he's an idiot.

10:10.610 --> 10:12.133
- Well, he's connected.

10:12.176 --> 10:16.006
And dangerous.

10:16.050 --> 10:20.358
Rumor is he's got an entire
arsenal stashed away.

10:20.402 --> 10:22.186
- He's also got giraffes.

10:24.362 --> 10:25.842
- I love giraffes.

10:25.886 --> 10:28.802
[percussive music]

10:28.845 --> 10:35.983
♪

10:43.164 --> 10:45.470
- [grunts]

10:45.514 --> 10:47.429
Aloha, ladies.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.215
[sighs]

10:51.259 --> 10:53.043
Thank you.

10:57.831 --> 11:00.790
- I have that shirt.
- Why am I not surprised?

11:00.834 --> 11:03.184
- Oh, hey there.

11:03.227 --> 11:05.490
- Sorry, have to search you
a little bit.

11:05.534 --> 11:07.449
Orders of Mr. Spivey.

11:08.842 --> 11:11.279
- Okay--[grunts]
Very good.

11:11.322 --> 11:12.802
See you bag, please?

11:12.846 --> 11:14.369
Oh, this is very nice.
- Thank you.

11:14.412 --> 11:16.676
- Okay.
Ooh.

11:18.721 --> 11:20.331
Freaky.
- [laughs]

11:20.375 --> 11:21.942
Not what you were expecting?

11:21.985 --> 11:25.467
- No, it's very good, it's just
most people--they have guns.

11:25.510 --> 11:27.904
Ah, a good look.
Okay.

11:27.948 --> 11:30.167
Señor.
Gracias.

11:30.211 --> 11:32.213
Welcome.
[Roy Orbison's "Go! Go! Go!"]

11:32.256 --> 11:34.998
- ♪ Well, you can't be
my loving baby ♪

11:35.042 --> 11:37.000
♪ You ain't got the style

11:37.044 --> 11:39.655
♪ I'm gonna get some
real gone love ♪

11:39.699 --> 11:41.831
♪ That'll drive
a cool cat wild ♪

11:41.875 --> 11:45.269
♪ We gotta move,
rollin' right on down ♪

11:45.313 --> 11:49.012
♪ Gonna get me a gal
that'll go out on the town ♪

11:49.056 --> 11:52.363
♪ Well you gotta move on
down the line ♪

11:52.407 --> 11:54.931
♪ I'm gonna get me a gal
that'll make some time ♪

11:54.975 --> 11:57.151
♪ She can't be square,
she can't be slow ♪

11:57.194 --> 11:58.718
♪ 'Cause when we start
struttin' ♪

11:58.761 --> 12:01.242
♪ Gotta go go go

12:01.285 --> 12:08.423
♪

12:09.076 --> 12:12.644
- All right, gentleman.
[indistinct]

12:12.688 --> 12:14.429
- Jesus.

12:14.472 --> 12:16.779
This place is a lot gaudier
than I thought.

12:16.823 --> 12:18.738
[laughs]
Look at this crowd.

12:20.914 --> 12:23.873
Archer Flournoy's on the board
of the phone company.

12:23.917 --> 12:26.702
He could help us locate
that cell.

12:26.746 --> 12:28.965
I just re-did his will.
Cut the kids out.

12:29.009 --> 12:31.446
It all goes to the dog.

12:31.489 --> 12:33.361
- Obviously.
- Jesus.

12:33.404 --> 12:34.666
The Staghornes are here.

12:34.710 --> 12:36.973
I'm not sure anybody's
seen them in daylight.

12:37.017 --> 12:38.627
James and Jimmy Jr.
own the "Chronicle,"

12:38.670 --> 12:40.672
which means they
pretty much control everything.

12:40.716 --> 12:43.414
- My stars.
Is that Allegra Dill?

12:43.458 --> 12:44.938
- I suppose

12:44.981 --> 12:47.592
they're letting everybody in
the front door these days.

12:47.636 --> 12:49.464
- Daddy.
[laughs]

12:49.507 --> 12:52.902
So I hear good things about
your senator, Miss Dill.

12:52.946 --> 12:54.904
It's impressive
how far you've come.

12:54.948 --> 12:57.646
- ♪ Go!

12:57.689 --> 13:01.606
[cheers and applause]

13:01.650 --> 13:03.478
- Pick!

13:03.521 --> 13:06.655
Yeah!
Spring break!

13:06.698 --> 13:09.092
Whoo-hoo!
[laughs]

13:09.136 --> 13:11.834
I didn't think you were coming.
Ha-ha!

13:11.878 --> 13:14.097
Yeah, boys, all right.

13:15.490 --> 13:16.839
Whoo!

13:16.883 --> 13:18.406
[sighs]

13:18.449 --> 13:19.886
[fast drumming]

13:19.929 --> 13:21.583
Hey, y'all hungry?

13:21.626 --> 13:24.847
I ordered a bunch of fish eggs
from fucking Tehran, but--

13:24.891 --> 13:27.589
[clears throat]
nobody's touched 'em.

13:27.632 --> 13:30.810
[coughs]

13:30.853 --> 13:33.987
[steel guitar playing]

13:34.030 --> 13:35.945
Who're you?

13:35.989 --> 13:38.165
- I'm her lawyer.
A.D. Singe.

13:38.208 --> 13:40.384
Like "scorch."
- You grow up rich or poor?

13:40.428 --> 13:42.212
- Middle class.

13:42.256 --> 13:45.259
- I'll bet you wanna see
my pet giraffes.

13:45.302 --> 13:47.435
- You bet right.

13:47.478 --> 13:51.308
♪

13:51.352 --> 13:53.833
- [chuckling]

13:54.921 --> 13:57.967
[sighs]
What's that look?

13:58.011 --> 14:00.100
- We need to talk.

14:00.143 --> 14:01.449
Alone.

14:01.492 --> 14:04.060
♪

14:07.063 --> 14:09.196
- This is Miss Daphne Owens.

14:09.239 --> 14:12.721
She, uh, balances the books
for these little shindigs.

14:12.764 --> 14:16.420
Miss Daffy, would you please
send a couple more mai tais

14:16.464 --> 14:18.596
out to the mayor?

14:18.640 --> 14:22.949
- The perfect circle
and the perfect crime.

14:22.992 --> 14:24.689
- You can't make it stick.

14:24.733 --> 14:25.777
- You don't have the proof.
- [chuckles]

14:25.821 --> 14:26.996
- Remember this shit?

14:27.040 --> 14:27.910
- That's where you're wrong,
Al.

14:27.954 --> 14:29.259
- Look at that.

14:29.303 --> 14:31.479
- I always show my work.

14:31.522 --> 14:33.437
- Still holds up.

14:34.569 --> 14:36.223
- A man broke into my room
last night.

14:36.266 --> 14:38.181
Took your worthless
deposition.

14:38.225 --> 14:40.488
Oh--first he choked me out.

14:48.626 --> 14:51.629
- Who was it?
- Who do you think?

14:51.673 --> 14:54.937
You gave it to me in public.
You set me up.

14:54.981 --> 14:56.460
So if you wanted Brattle

14:56.504 --> 14:59.550
to know that
you were cooperating...

14:59.594 --> 15:01.161
congratulations.

15:01.204 --> 15:06.035
- I had no idea that Brattle
would send his boys after you.

15:06.079 --> 15:08.211
You were supposed to hand it
off to your boss.

15:08.255 --> 15:10.039
- What's your game?

15:10.083 --> 15:13.347
He's a psychopath,
and you want him here?

15:15.001 --> 15:17.394
- [sighs]

15:17.438 --> 15:20.223
I didn't trust the FBI to catch
that old goat.

15:22.095 --> 15:24.401
And I was right.
[chuckles]

15:25.968 --> 15:28.275
Well, so what'd your bosses say

15:28.318 --> 15:29.972
when you told 'em
old Clyde was here?

15:36.761 --> 15:39.939
You didn't tell them,
did you?

15:39.982 --> 15:41.592
Well, well, well.

15:41.636 --> 15:44.465
I guess you still got
a soft spot for me after all.

15:44.508 --> 15:47.076
- The only soft spot is the one
on your thick skull.

15:47.120 --> 15:49.122
- [laughs]

15:49.165 --> 15:50.732
- A clean deposition
is your one chance

15:50.775 --> 15:52.429
to keep your assets unfrozen
and your ass

15:52.473 --> 15:54.649
out of federal prison.
- [sighs]

15:54.692 --> 15:57.608
- The committee knows American
weapons went missing in Syria,

15:57.652 --> 15:59.828
that you were there,
and then you got rich.

15:59.871 --> 16:02.396
So you either tie Brattle
to it,

16:02.439 --> 16:05.007
or the noose
goes around your neck.

16:08.228 --> 16:10.273
- Well, your date seems cool.

16:10.317 --> 16:13.059
- He's not cool.
He's my lawyer.

16:15.670 --> 16:18.629
- If you could just
unlock the account,

16:18.673 --> 16:22.807
I'll be able to solve my
client's problems right away.

16:22.851 --> 16:24.374
Now taste that

16:24.418 --> 16:27.508
and tell me that ain't
the best drink you ever had.

16:28.857 --> 16:31.381
- I suppose I could
make a call.

16:31.425 --> 16:33.470
You did such good work
on my will.

16:33.514 --> 16:34.819
- Thank you.

16:34.863 --> 16:36.473
- But the thing is,

16:36.517 --> 16:40.129
this is my day off.
I have a drink in my hand.

16:40.173 --> 16:43.263
And most of all,
I just don't wanna.

16:46.048 --> 16:49.008
[harp melody]

16:49.051 --> 16:50.966
♪

16:51.010 --> 16:54.056
- ♪ Listen to my call

16:54.100 --> 16:55.536
- You're barking up the wrong
tree.

16:56.754 --> 16:57.842
You don't mind.

16:57.886 --> 16:59.540
- Uh, no.
Go ahead.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.150
♪

17:01.194 --> 17:04.980
- The only thing rich men
respond to is fear.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.155
Guess you're not afraid.

17:06.199 --> 17:07.591
- I guess I'm not rich.

17:07.635 --> 17:09.854
- [laughs]

17:09.898 --> 17:12.031
I'm Lucretia.

17:12.074 --> 17:13.641
- I'm A.D. Singe.

17:13.684 --> 17:15.686
- Tried to hire you
as my divorce lawyer,

17:15.730 --> 17:17.906
but they said
you don't swing that way.

17:17.949 --> 17:20.039
- Well, I'm only employable
when somebody dies.

17:20.082 --> 17:21.736
- [laughs]

17:21.779 --> 17:24.173
- And you?
- [sighs]

17:24.217 --> 17:26.175
I'm just a woman on the verge.

17:26.219 --> 17:28.047
- Verge of what?
- Mm, something big.

17:28.090 --> 17:30.136
A hangover probably.

17:30.179 --> 17:32.312
[chuckles]

17:32.355 --> 17:37.534
It is so nice to see all these
men out with their mistresses.

17:37.578 --> 17:40.537
Oh, he probably picked her up
at the train station.

17:40.581 --> 17:41.930
- [laughs]

17:41.973 --> 17:44.367
- Yeah, he'll send her back
to Lubbock with the clap

17:44.411 --> 17:47.805
and a gift card
to a spaghetti restaurant.

17:47.849 --> 17:49.894
I know when people are cheating

17:49.938 --> 17:53.420
because I'm a grade-A sneak.

17:53.463 --> 17:56.075
I've got tools,
and I am willing to use them.

17:56.118 --> 17:57.815
Don't you cross me.

17:57.859 --> 18:01.123
♪

18:01.167 --> 18:03.560
- What if I got some sneaking
of my own to do?

18:03.604 --> 18:06.302
- Well, Mr. Lawyer Man,
why don't you come out

18:06.346 --> 18:09.349
from behind that bar
and tell me all about it?

18:10.785 --> 18:13.440
- What do you know
about those bombs?

18:15.703 --> 18:18.140
- The bombs?
- The one that killed Felicity.

18:18.184 --> 18:20.360
And the one
that almost killed me.

18:20.403 --> 18:22.492
- Pick, you actually think
I set those bombs?

18:22.536 --> 18:25.800
- You are a weapons dealer.
- I was a weapons dealer.

18:27.236 --> 18:29.282
Don't you fucking do that,
Pick.

18:31.022 --> 18:32.633
We're family.

18:34.722 --> 18:37.377
And just so you know--

18:37.420 --> 18:39.770
I'm no bomber.
- Then who is?

18:39.814 --> 18:41.642
- Well, I don't know,
but I'll tell you this.

18:42.512 --> 18:44.732
- Bombers, they light a fuse,

18:44.775 --> 18:48.823
and they walk away 'cause
they're chickenshit cowards.

18:48.866 --> 18:50.520
I have to kill a man...

18:52.131 --> 18:54.524
I look him in the eye.

18:55.873 --> 18:57.397
[door opens]

18:57.440 --> 18:59.877
- [tired breathing]

18:59.921 --> 19:01.575
Hello, Jay.

19:01.618 --> 19:02.967
And...

19:03.011 --> 19:05.448
lady in a suit.

19:05.492 --> 19:08.190
This appears not to be
the commode.

19:10.497 --> 19:12.281
- Mr. Mayor.
- Hmm?

19:12.325 --> 19:14.631
- Won't you
join me outside?

19:14.675 --> 19:18.157
We can't deny our guests
the pleasure of your company.

19:18.200 --> 19:19.636
Heh.
- [laughs]

19:19.680 --> 19:21.290
Oh, and besides,

19:21.334 --> 19:22.987
I think a couple
of them hula girls

19:23.031 --> 19:25.164
are about to shed their grass
skirts if you catch my meaning.

19:25.207 --> 19:27.383
[laughs]
- Hey, hey.

19:28.515 --> 19:31.213
[luau music]

19:31.257 --> 19:33.084
♪

19:33.128 --> 19:35.913
- Testing, testing.
[chuckles]

19:35.957 --> 19:39.178
This thing on?
Well, thank you all for coming.

19:39.221 --> 19:40.614
Hey, let's give it up
for Carvell,

19:40.657 --> 19:42.398
our county's
youngest Old Elvis.

19:42.442 --> 19:45.009
- Way to go, kid!
[cheers and applause]

19:45.053 --> 19:46.315
- Who is that man?

19:46.359 --> 19:48.361
- That's Jake Spivey, Daddy.

19:48.404 --> 19:50.363
He owns the house now.
He's new.

19:50.406 --> 19:51.842
- All right, now...
- Christ.

19:51.886 --> 19:54.367
- Let's get to the real reason
that we're here,

19:54.410 --> 19:58.849
which is to support
our dear friend

19:58.893 --> 20:00.764
Mayor Antonio Salazar,

20:00.808 --> 20:04.159
on his fourth consecutive
re-election campaign!

20:04.203 --> 20:05.508
Come on, y'all!

20:05.552 --> 20:07.249
- [laughs]
[cheers and applause]

20:07.293 --> 20:08.729
- Hey, Big Tony,

20:08.772 --> 20:11.035
why don't you come up here
and give a speech, man?

20:11.079 --> 20:12.341
Aw, don't you get modest.

20:12.385 --> 20:13.864
Get on up here.
Speech!

20:13.908 --> 20:15.605
Speech--come on, y'all!
Speech!

20:15.649 --> 20:17.694
[applause]
- All right.

20:17.738 --> 20:18.652
All right.

20:21.176 --> 20:22.699
- He can't walk
a straight line.

20:22.743 --> 20:24.745
- Daddy, he's been
a good friend to us.

20:24.788 --> 20:25.876
- I don't care.

20:25.920 --> 20:27.661
- Our mayor,
ladies and gentlemen.

20:27.704 --> 20:29.880
- Aw, well this is a surprise!

20:29.924 --> 20:32.492
I thought this was
supposed to be a party.

20:32.535 --> 20:35.277
Ah, boop, bop, bee, doop, bop,
boop, boop, boop!

20:35.321 --> 20:37.192
[laughs]

20:37.236 --> 20:39.368
I love a party!

20:39.412 --> 20:41.283
It's a--it's an honor

20:41.327 --> 20:43.764
being mayor
of this beautiful town

20:43.807 --> 20:46.506
and all of its beautiful
citizens.

20:46.549 --> 20:47.898
- Most of these people
are trash.

20:47.942 --> 20:49.160
- Shh.

20:49.204 --> 20:50.727
- Of course, not all of them
are beautiful.

20:50.771 --> 20:54.514
I was on Main today, and I saw
a lady who was a real horse.

20:54.557 --> 20:56.777
[laughs]
[crowd murmurs]

20:56.820 --> 21:00.389
But horses have their uses too.

21:00.433 --> 21:02.086
Right?
- Mmm.

21:02.130 --> 21:04.393
- Transportation is one.

21:04.437 --> 21:06.656
You know?
And then...

21:06.700 --> 21:08.092
glue.

21:08.136 --> 21:09.572
Eventually, I suppose.

21:09.616 --> 21:11.748
- Pull yourself together, pal.
- Shh.

21:11.792 --> 21:13.968
- And what's the glue
that bonds us all?

21:14.011 --> 21:17.363
Well, it's business.
Today it's my business

21:17.406 --> 21:19.843
to keep you safe
from the bomber out there...

21:19.887 --> 21:21.018
- Hey.

21:21.062 --> 21:22.324
- By keeping the drinks
flowing in here.

21:22.368 --> 21:23.412
- Why don't you give me
that phone number?

21:23.456 --> 21:25.284
- So drink up!
- The missing blower?

21:25.327 --> 21:28.112
- ...I will sit down.

21:28.156 --> 21:29.549
[applause]

21:29.592 --> 21:31.290
- Get him outta here.
- Now, now.

21:31.333 --> 21:32.726
Just let him have his--

21:32.769 --> 21:33.770
- That's the way to get 'em,
Mayor.

21:33.814 --> 21:35.555
- Shh.
- That's winning 'em over.

21:35.598 --> 21:36.991
- Please.
- [snickering]

21:37.034 --> 21:40.647
- Nothing rattles men more
than a crying woman.

21:41.691 --> 21:45.304
[clears throat]
Oh, no.

21:45.347 --> 21:48.698
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

21:48.742 --> 21:51.440
- What happened!?
- Donna!

21:51.484 --> 21:53.834
My 12-year-old Donna--

21:53.877 --> 21:55.792
she's out there somewhere!
Shit!

21:55.836 --> 21:57.446
- Are you sure
she's not at home?

21:57.490 --> 21:59.405
- She wasn't there
when I left!

21:59.448 --> 22:01.624
What if she gets caught
by the car bomber,

22:01.668 --> 22:05.715
and I'm here just drinking,
and--I gotta find her.

22:05.759 --> 22:08.588
She's not answering her phone.
If I just knew she was indoors!

22:08.631 --> 22:11.460
And safe!
[cries]

22:11.504 --> 22:14.594
What if he car bombs her?

22:14.637 --> 22:16.683
[crying]
- Here.

22:16.726 --> 22:18.946
Let me fix this.
- Okay.

22:18.989 --> 22:20.687
- I'm still the mayor,
aren't I?

22:20.730 --> 22:22.253
- Yeah.
- Okay.

22:22.297 --> 22:23.385
- Uh-huh.

22:23.429 --> 22:25.039
- Now let's you, me
have a daiquiri.

22:25.082 --> 22:26.170
- Okay.
- Okay?

22:26.214 --> 22:27.476
- Yeah.

22:27.520 --> 22:29.130
- I'll make a call.
- Yeah.

22:29.173 --> 22:31.480
- We'll see if we can't find
Donna's phone.

22:31.524 --> 22:33.961
- Okay.
- Just take a deep breath.

22:34.004 --> 22:35.832
- Would you like me
to get you some shrimp?

22:36.877 --> 22:39.793
- I got you.
What do I need shrimp for?

22:39.836 --> 22:40.924
- Fruit?

22:40.968 --> 22:42.012
Would you like me
to get you some fruit?

22:42.056 --> 22:44.711
- I got you.
What do I need fruit for?

22:50.238 --> 22:51.413
- Here.

22:51.457 --> 22:53.415
Put this in your GPS
or whatever.

22:53.459 --> 22:54.677
I don't know how
your car works.

22:54.721 --> 22:56.810
[chuckles]
- Is there a Donna?

22:56.853 --> 22:59.160
- Donna's my 12-year-old cat.
- [laughs]

22:59.203 --> 23:01.858
- She doesn't have a phone,
but she is missing.

23:01.902 --> 23:05.471
Who's the dame?
- Allegra Dill.

23:05.514 --> 23:08.561
[dramatic music]

23:08.604 --> 23:10.127
- I know you.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.915
You're my husband's dead
fiancé's sister.

23:14.958 --> 23:21.617
♪

23:21.661 --> 23:23.750
Very nice meeting you.

23:30.365 --> 23:33.412
- Lucretia Colder?
- I guess so.

23:36.763 --> 23:39.287
- Let's go find that phone.

23:39.330 --> 23:42.246
[tense music]

23:42.290 --> 23:46.816
♪

23:46.860 --> 23:49.079
- Her burner phone
is at Lupe's?

23:49.123 --> 23:52.082
[sign squeaks]

23:52.126 --> 23:55.434
- Hi, um.
I'm looking for a cell phone.

23:55.477 --> 23:58.654
Uh, uh--
lost and found.

23:58.698 --> 24:01.614
Thank you.
Excuse me.

24:01.657 --> 24:04.268
♪

24:04.312 --> 24:06.445
Is this it?
Is this all you have?

24:06.488 --> 24:09.578
Um, uh, cell phone?
Teléfono?

24:09.622 --> 24:12.320
This.
No, no, cell phone.

24:12.363 --> 24:13.974
Can I look?

24:14.017 --> 24:15.889
Are you always here?
Is there someone else?

24:15.932 --> 24:17.760
Have you seen a cell phone?
- Lo siento.

24:17.804 --> 24:19.762
- Any kind of cell phone?
Celular?

24:19.806 --> 24:21.808
Anyone left anything?
Uh, teléfono?

24:21.851 --> 24:25.028
Like, maybe heard some ringing?

24:25.072 --> 24:26.552
[sighs]

24:26.595 --> 24:33.036
♪

24:33.080 --> 24:34.473
- Allegra.

24:34.516 --> 24:36.823
You got to cool off.

24:38.607 --> 24:39.869
Sorry.
It's okay.

24:39.913 --> 24:41.262
It's okay.

24:41.305 --> 24:42.742
We hit a dead end, but
we're gonna keep trying, okay?

24:42.785 --> 24:44.613
We gonna try again.
- No.

24:44.657 --> 24:46.659
It's here.
It has to be here.

24:46.702 --> 24:48.530
- Okay, can we both
just calm down though?

24:48.574 --> 24:50.619
- No!

24:50.663 --> 24:53.535
[soft dramatic music]

24:53.579 --> 25:00.716
♪

25:54.596 --> 25:56.076
I knew it.

26:03.605 --> 26:05.172
I knew it.

26:06.303 --> 26:07.566
- You were right.

26:09.655 --> 26:11.744
- This is where she lived.

26:12.745 --> 26:14.834
Where she really lived.

27:03.186 --> 27:04.797
- [laughs]

27:07.016 --> 27:08.975
[laughs]

27:21.335 --> 27:22.771
- Allegra.

27:24.817 --> 27:26.906
- Any luck?

27:26.949 --> 27:28.995
- Nope.
It's wiped.

27:29.038 --> 27:31.258
Whatever she's working on,
she didn't leave a trace.

27:31.301 --> 27:33.173
- She wasn't safe.

27:34.870 --> 27:36.698
Not even here.

27:41.529 --> 27:43.270
Never should've left her alone.

27:53.367 --> 27:55.064
[sighs]

27:58.851 --> 28:01.810
[mysterious music]

28:01.854 --> 28:08.991
♪

28:13.561 --> 28:15.258
You're Harold Snow.

28:15.302 --> 28:16.912
- Yeah.

28:16.956 --> 28:19.175
- What the hell are you doing
in my dead sister's apartment?

28:19.219 --> 28:22.135
- Well, I could ask you
the same thing.

28:27.227 --> 28:29.882
[sign squeaking]

28:29.925 --> 28:33.755
[tape stretching]

28:33.799 --> 28:35.278
- Hey.

28:35.322 --> 28:39.021
Aw, lady,
what'd I ever do to you?

28:39.065 --> 28:41.023
Oh, man.
- Search his toolbox.

28:41.067 --> 28:42.808
- Hey.
Come on, now.

28:42.851 --> 28:45.898
Can't we all just
talk this out like adults?

28:45.941 --> 28:49.379
- Sure.
Why are you here?

28:49.423 --> 28:52.165
- Why are any of us here?

28:52.208 --> 28:54.254
Our existence is--
- Is this loaded?

28:54.297 --> 28:56.038
- I don't know.

28:56.082 --> 28:58.649
I don't know.
Did you put that in there?

28:58.693 --> 28:59.781
- We're gonna tell the cops

28:59.825 --> 29:01.304
that we surprised you
in a burglary.

29:01.348 --> 29:03.654
I took this away from you,
and I shot you in the knee.

29:03.698 --> 29:04.917
- Hey, hey!
- The right one I think.

29:04.960 --> 29:06.875
- You just can't go around
shooting people.

29:06.919 --> 29:09.225
Even in this town!
- Is that so?

29:09.269 --> 29:12.011
- Yeah.
- Harold, uh, I am a lawyer,

29:12.054 --> 29:14.100
and you have several options
available to you.

29:14.143 --> 29:15.449
None of them are ideal.

29:15.492 --> 29:16.667
[gunshot]
- [cries]

29:16.711 --> 29:17.843
Jesus.

29:17.886 --> 29:19.714
Good God!

29:19.758 --> 29:22.195
What the fuck?
- Why are you here?

29:22.238 --> 29:23.892
- I'm just looking
for my bug!

29:23.936 --> 29:25.459
- Your bug?
- Yeah.

29:25.502 --> 29:28.070
My little baby--

29:28.114 --> 29:31.857
it's a black box recorder.
Fits in your hand.

29:31.900 --> 29:33.336
It don't matter anyhow.

29:33.380 --> 29:35.382
Some asshole broke in here
and stole it.

29:35.425 --> 29:36.905
It was pricey as hell,

29:36.949 --> 29:39.342
and I spent a shit ton
of billable hours

29:39.386 --> 29:41.431
making sure everything
was encrypted.

29:41.475 --> 29:42.432
Psh.

29:42.476 --> 29:44.739
I'm probably out
at least a grand.

29:44.783 --> 29:46.567
So rest assured,

29:46.610 --> 29:49.700
you're not the one
having a bad day here, okay?

29:49.744 --> 29:51.224
- You're a creep, Harold.

29:51.267 --> 29:53.356
But you're a business man.

29:53.400 --> 29:56.969
Who paid you to bug
your landlady?

29:57.012 --> 29:58.492
- Can I smoke?

29:59.841 --> 30:01.103
Please.

30:01.147 --> 30:02.452
I know you got cigarettes
in there.

30:02.496 --> 30:03.845
- [groans]

30:03.889 --> 30:06.935
- My ears are ringing.
Just FYI.

30:06.979 --> 30:09.068
- Don't be dumb, Harold.

30:14.638 --> 30:16.031
You're not too smart.

30:17.076 --> 30:19.992
But you're not dumb either.

30:20.035 --> 30:21.863
Who paid you?

30:21.907 --> 30:23.734
- If you wanna know so bad,

30:23.778 --> 30:26.825
it seems to me it might be
worth something to you.

30:29.001 --> 30:31.830
Fuck!
God damn it!

30:31.873 --> 30:34.963
You're an ass--
[blows]

30:35.007 --> 30:36.530
You're an asshole.

30:36.573 --> 30:37.879
Ow.

30:37.923 --> 30:40.926
It was Ferness.

30:40.969 --> 30:42.144
The ex.

30:42.188 --> 30:43.667
- Floyd Ferness?
- Yeah.

30:43.711 --> 30:46.235
I caught her one night
banging on her door.

30:46.279 --> 30:49.978
Said he wasn't jealous,
he was just worried.

30:50.022 --> 30:52.328
Yeah.
I heard that one before.

30:52.372 --> 30:54.853
So I told him that
there were certain services

30:54.896 --> 30:56.332
I could provide.

30:56.376 --> 30:57.986
- You spy on people for money.

30:58.030 --> 31:00.249
- Hey, look, man.
I just--

31:00.293 --> 31:02.425
I help people
get what they want.

31:02.469 --> 31:05.124
And jerks like Ferness,
how do they pay me back?

31:05.167 --> 31:08.214
They steal my shit.
Life's a trip.

31:10.129 --> 31:12.218
Look, I'm sorry he maybe...

31:14.089 --> 31:16.004
Blew up your sister.

31:16.048 --> 31:17.266
- [sighs]
- She was cool.

31:17.310 --> 31:19.747
We had a nice repartée.

31:19.790 --> 31:22.184
She and I loved to laugh.

31:22.228 --> 31:24.839
I know it ain't my place
in saying it,

31:24.883 --> 31:27.146
but maybe...

31:27.189 --> 31:29.888
maybe you should've
taken better care of her.

31:29.931 --> 31:32.891
[tense music]

31:32.934 --> 31:34.718
♪

31:34.762 --> 31:36.938
I struck a nerve, huh?

31:36.982 --> 31:43.945
♪

31:43.989 --> 31:45.947
Whoa.
Hey, now.

31:45.991 --> 31:47.340
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Okay.

31:47.383 --> 31:48.994
- Allegra, you don't--
- Hey, hey, look.

31:49.037 --> 31:52.040
We don't have to go there.
You gonna stab me?

31:52.084 --> 31:54.434
Man, are you cool with this?

31:54.477 --> 31:56.958
You gonna watch this?
You gonna watch her kill me?

31:57.002 --> 31:58.394
You gonna--
[tape splits]

32:02.181 --> 32:04.966
Ow.
God damn.

32:05.010 --> 32:07.099
- Get out.
- Gladly.

32:08.839 --> 32:11.277
Jesus.
[grunts]

32:13.453 --> 32:14.933
Ow.

32:17.152 --> 32:20.286
About next month's rent--
- It's covered.

32:21.026 --> 32:23.985
Sweet.
Can I--can I get my gun back?

32:24.029 --> 32:26.074
- Get out.
- All right.

32:27.032 --> 32:28.947
[door opens]

32:38.957 --> 32:40.697
[door slams]

32:40.741 --> 32:43.483
[dramatic music]

32:43.526 --> 32:44.963
♪

32:45.006 --> 32:47.269
- We can get that recording
from Floyd,

32:47.313 --> 32:48.967
we can find out
what she's doing--

32:49.010 --> 32:51.752
what kind of danger
she was in.

32:51.795 --> 32:54.973
- What was that in there?
- That was a lucky break.

32:55.016 --> 32:56.278
It establishes behavior.

32:56.322 --> 32:59.238
- And what is it
that you do exactly?

33:00.587 --> 33:03.285
- I'm an investigator.
- Right.

33:03.329 --> 33:05.505
And these your usual methods?

33:05.548 --> 33:07.594
- When necessary.

33:07.637 --> 33:09.030
- And then what?

33:09.074 --> 33:11.815
- Once I have the facts,
I hand them over.

33:11.859 --> 33:15.428
- [laughs] And then what?
You just--you just walk away?

33:15.471 --> 33:16.777
- Usually.

33:16.820 --> 33:19.475
Unless there's something
worth sticking around for.

33:19.519 --> 33:21.738
Come on,
let's hit the Slush Pit.

33:21.782 --> 33:23.349
We can talk strategy.

33:23.392 --> 33:27.179
- Uh, as much as I would love
to get a drink with you...

33:28.658 --> 33:31.096
I think we both need some sleep
for the funeral tomorrow.

33:34.099 --> 33:35.709
- Right.

33:39.234 --> 33:41.062
I'm gonna walk.

33:42.890 --> 33:44.283
See you tomorrow.

33:48.896 --> 33:50.637
[car engine starts]

34:01.517 --> 34:03.519
Hey, Lalo.

34:03.563 --> 34:05.347
- Allegra.

34:05.391 --> 34:07.958
- Since when are you
border patrol?

34:08.002 --> 34:09.525
- A couple years now.

34:09.569 --> 34:11.527
I still help my dad
back out at the club.

34:11.571 --> 34:13.355
You know?

34:13.399 --> 34:15.183
Gotta climb the ladder somehow,
right?

34:15.227 --> 34:18.143
So I can be like you.

34:21.929 --> 34:23.409
Allegra!

34:28.240 --> 34:29.719
Hey, you want a ride somewhere?

34:29.763 --> 34:32.679
They, uh, say there's a killer
on the loose.

34:35.508 --> 34:38.554
[car engine starts]
- One bombing at the zoo.

34:38.598 --> 34:40.556
There are two bombings
of police officers,

34:40.600 --> 34:42.819
and these bombings...
- Um...

34:42.863 --> 34:44.908
- Are clearly
the symptom of a deeper rot.

34:44.952 --> 34:46.388
- No thanks. I need a walk.
- Thousands of years ago,

34:46.432 --> 34:47.998
Egyptian priests would...
- Okay, then.

34:48.042 --> 34:49.913
- Remove dead men's brains
through the nose...

34:49.957 --> 34:51.263
- Stay safe.
- You too.

34:51.306 --> 34:53.091
- By using a sort
of curved hook.

34:53.134 --> 34:55.658
My friends today, that hook
is called capitalism,

34:55.702 --> 34:58.313
and it is removing your brain.

34:58.357 --> 35:00.707
[eerie music]

35:00.750 --> 35:02.143
- [grunting]

35:02.187 --> 35:06.974
♪

35:07.017 --> 35:10.108
[heavy breathing]

35:36.221 --> 35:37.526
[computer beeps]

35:37.570 --> 35:39.441
- Guess who encrypted
all his shit.

35:41.139 --> 35:42.618
- Hi.

35:44.272 --> 35:46.579
Are you gonna hurt me?

35:49.190 --> 35:52.150
[moody jazz music]

35:52.193 --> 35:53.977
- And he took the computer?

35:54.021 --> 35:56.458
♪

35:56.502 --> 35:58.808
Any indication
of where he was going?

35:58.852 --> 36:01.898
♪

36:01.942 --> 36:03.857
Did he seem upset?

36:08.731 --> 36:10.777
Are there any vehicles missing?

36:10.820 --> 36:17.740
♪

36:28.795 --> 36:31.754
[ominous music]

36:31.798 --> 36:38.718
♪

36:47.248 --> 36:49.250
[tires screech]

37:03.351 --> 37:05.745
- Mister Brattle.

37:12.491 --> 37:15.407
[ominous music builds]

37:15.450 --> 37:20.412
♪

37:25.155 --> 37:27.070
- I apologize
for having to search you,

37:27.114 --> 37:28.681
but I'm sure you'll understand.

37:31.249 --> 37:32.554
- Still,

37:32.598 --> 37:37.211
this seems a little bit
out of the ordinary.

37:37.255 --> 37:39.866
[mysterious music]

37:39.909 --> 37:42.869
When did humble Senate
staffers start packing heat?

37:43.826 --> 37:47.090
Oh, thank you.
That's Harley.

37:47.134 --> 37:49.310
He's been with the company
for more than a decade.

37:49.354 --> 37:51.356
He's a good boy.

37:51.399 --> 37:54.489
And I believe you met Sid.

37:54.533 --> 37:57.318
- How's your throat?
- Still a little sore.

37:57.362 --> 38:00.103
- You came back
at the wrong time.

38:00.147 --> 38:01.844
- That's Anatol driving.

38:01.888 --> 38:05.326
He's, uh,
a little less delicate.

38:05.370 --> 38:09.374
♪

38:09.417 --> 38:12.290
I was sorry to hear
about your sister,

38:12.333 --> 38:14.292
but I appreciate
your professionalism

38:14.335 --> 38:15.945
in the face of tragedy.

38:15.989 --> 38:21.690
I always found work to be a
balm when life became too much.

38:21.734 --> 38:24.563
- Work?
Is that what you call

38:24.606 --> 38:26.695
stealing $40 million
in American guns?

38:26.739 --> 38:30.046
- [chuckles] That is simply
inaccurate, my dear.

38:30.090 --> 38:32.310
I reclaimed those guns.

38:32.353 --> 38:35.661
And then I sold them for quite
a bit more than that.

38:36.618 --> 38:38.620
It's a good thing
that your senator

38:38.664 --> 38:41.449
is moving forward
with the public hearing.

38:41.493 --> 38:43.625
He has a chance
to clear things up.

38:43.669 --> 38:48.326
Especially now
the situation's so, uh, fluid.

38:48.369 --> 38:50.153
- What is it that you want,
Clyde?

38:50.197 --> 38:54.941
- Well, Miss Dill, you might
say I want to take my medicine.

38:56.421 --> 38:57.813
- Are you serious?

39:00.468 --> 39:02.340
How much medicine?

39:02.383 --> 39:04.429
- Let's say a few years

39:04.472 --> 39:07.562
in one of the more relaxed
federal hoosegows,

39:07.606 --> 39:10.435
and a fine of, well, no more
than two or three million.

39:10.478 --> 39:11.871
- Two years instead of life?

39:11.914 --> 39:13.916
- Life is such
an indeterminate sentence.

39:13.960 --> 39:17.224
- It's not enough.
The senator needs scalps.

39:17.267 --> 39:20.662
- Even an amateur knows not to
play his hand before the call.

39:20.706 --> 39:22.403
- And what if you're bluffing?

39:24.144 --> 39:26.102
- I don't bluff.

39:26.146 --> 39:27.452
- Tell about Jake, boss.

39:27.495 --> 39:30.324
- Oh, yes.
Jake.

39:30.368 --> 39:33.066
- He says he's retired.
- That's what he's calling it?

39:33.109 --> 39:35.677
Well, I'm sorry to tell you

39:35.721 --> 39:39.377
that Jake has done
some terrible things.

39:39.420 --> 39:43.206
Terrible, awful,
shocking things.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.731
- He's bad, all right.
- Unspeakable deeds...

39:48.168 --> 39:50.083
And I can prove them all.

39:52.477 --> 39:54.566
Ever heard of Al-Namur?

39:56.089 --> 39:58.396
- What about you, Clyde?

39:58.439 --> 39:59.962
What about your deeds?

40:00.006 --> 40:02.051
- You know, it's funny.
For nearly 30 years

40:02.095 --> 40:03.183
our government found

40:03.226 --> 40:05.577
my particular
set of skills useful.

40:07.013 --> 40:09.494
Now they consider them
indictable.

40:18.546 --> 40:21.114
[tense music]

40:21.157 --> 40:23.638
- If you're taking me
to my hotel, you missed a turn.

40:23.682 --> 40:26.119
- No, we're not taking you
to our hotel.

40:26.162 --> 40:27.555
♪

40:27.599 --> 40:29.775
[chortling]

40:31.037 --> 40:33.213
I'm gonna give you some advice,
Miss Dill.

40:33.256 --> 40:35.650
What I'm gonna tell you
took me years to learn.

40:35.694 --> 40:37.173
It's very simple,
and it's simply this:

40:37.217 --> 40:42.004
do not believe a word
Jake Spivey says.

40:42.048 --> 40:48.968
♪

40:54.626 --> 40:56.715
Something I want you to see.

41:22.741 --> 41:25.961
[ominous music]

41:26.005 --> 41:32.925
♪

42:11.790 --> 42:15.271
[electrical buzzing]

42:34.682 --> 42:36.162
[thump]

42:36.205 --> 42:39.339
[footsteps]

42:41.254 --> 42:43.169
[buzzing]

42:46.433 --> 42:49.131
[beeping]

42:54.180 --> 42:57.096
[blades whirring]
